<subSubSection id="4392EA1055F80A70A3F66914591912FD" type="nomenclature">
<taxonomicName id="0D41ED3890FBA3BED69C0FF675E2CCB5" authority="Pickford, 1991" authorityName="Pickford" authorityYear="1991" class="Mammalia" family="Anthracotheriidae" genus="Afromeryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="grex">Afromeryx grex</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3D9E9D46D8C1761BCFA43C7910F49720" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1B192CE61F0946A0BD5E5CCC135149E1" type="description">
<paragraph id="E5AF0EB8899FE045F508E02A1FC3307B" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" type="mainText">Type.-M 15021, sub-adult left dentary, edentulous symphysis, crowns of p2-m3, m3 in crypt (Table 1, Fig. 5A).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="580CC83031E75EC7891E1C67A4BDD973" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="52F4C67BDC38AF7298D303E7952BFDC6" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" type="mainText">
Diagnosis.-Differs from 
<taxonomicName id="C4241ADF0B5B6AD117B70B7A4E9BB5A3" authority="Pickford, 1991" authorityName="Pickford" authorityYear="1991" class="Mammalia" family="Anthracotheriidae" genus="Afromeryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zelteni">A. zelteni</taxonomicName>
in being larger (m2 area&gt;60% larger), having a much longer molar series length (m1-3 ~ 108 mm in 
<taxonomicName id="90A6C0BE4ECC58D5DDB212A8ABE0F67B" authority="Pickford, 1991" authorityName="Pickford" authorityYear="1991" class="Mammalia" family="Anthracotheriidae" genus="Afromeryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="grex">A. grex</taxonomicName>
versus ~58 mm in 
<taxonomicName id="5BD33B1C445AD471B47E0256D674C1A7" authority="Pickford, 1991" authorityName="Pickford" authorityYear="1991" class="Mammalia" family="Anthracotheriidae" genus="Afromeryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zelteni">A. zelteni</taxonomicName>
), p4 with a well-developed talonid; differs from 
<taxonomicName id="CB6D6077CA2E3385B1142D01B333B6D3" authority="Pickford, 1991" authorityName="Pickford" authorityYear="1991" class="Mammalia" family="Anthracotheriidae" genus="Afromeryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="palustris">A. palustris</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicNameLabel id="61634FD1374FCF272FF7ECFE09E12BC0" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
below) in having smaller premolars (~25-30%), lower premolars with pustulate anterior and posterior crests, lowers premolars with distinct and elevated cingulids, p2 lacks development of an anterior crest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5ED0D18AC00BD4176DFF47AF32E731C7" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="1A1FBE2CC68083697DF851CA7B67263D" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" type="mainText">Etymology.-&quot;Grex,&quot; Greek for flock or herd, in recognition of the herd behavior of many artiodactyls.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0074427B38BC1E18A7614AC9618603FF" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="1A838A738E69FC50C82CCEDD0C938F72" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" type="mainText">Occurrence.-Early Miocene, Wadi Moghra, Egypt.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0B87ED87A7EE1992C9BAE5FD959CE99D" type="description">
<paragraph id="DA17373DB3A98519883A5709D68922DF" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" type="mainText">Description.-Description of holotype specimen and occlusal details of teeth are available in Pickford (1991).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="87C80111275DB72932F1EE57FBEC3271" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5F073BE56E2B34FB378EC4C3C0E5518A" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" type="mainText">
Remarks.-
<taxonomicName id="FC5404365A9A12D20307C1C149EFE86A" authority="Pickford, 1991" authorityName="Pickford" authorityYear="1991" class="Mammalia" family="Anthracotheriidae" genus="Afromeryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="grex">Afromeryx grex</taxonomicName>
resembles the better known 
<taxonomicName id="E681CF14E2092A9A4E260B6601A48892" authority="Pickford, 1991" authorityName="Pickford" authorityYear="1991" class="Mammalia" family="Anthracotheriidae" genus="Afromeryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zelteni">A. zelteni</taxonomicName>
from Gebel Zelten, in having an unfused symphysis, dental formula 3.1.4.3; no specializations of the anterior dentition, i1-3 are small spatulate teeth; no i3-c diastema, c-p1 diastema present, p1 single rooted, and mental foramina below i1, p2, p4. in all known comparable parts, 
<taxonomicName id="F798423A20B6C52BF93BFCD38EFE0294" authority="Pickford, 1991" authorityName="Pickford" authorityYear="1991" class="Mammalia" family="Anthracotheriidae" genus="Afromeryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="grex">A. grex</taxonomicName>
seems to be a larger version of 
<taxonomicName id="B107FA1135413C6DDED8BF85D23485BD" authority="Pickford, 1991" authorityName="Pickford" authorityYear="1991" class="Mammalia" family="Anthracotheriidae" genus="Afromeryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zelteni">A. zelteni</taxonomicName>
. As Pickford (1991) noted, the presence of pustulate crests on the premolars in species of 
<taxonomicName id="8FB4DDCFA29817F78C5959AC81147CC7" authority="Pickford, 1991" authorityName="Pickford" authorityYear="1991" class="Mammalia" family="Anthracotheriidae" genus="Afromeryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Afromeryx</taxonomicName>
is reminiscent of the condition seen in 
<taxonomicName id="56C685C62D1023550D353951213946B0" authority="Pilgrim, 1908" authorityName="Pilgrim" authorityYear="1908" class="Mammalia" family="Anthracotheriidae" genus="Gonotelma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="shabazi">Gonotelma shabazi</taxonomicName>
from the Bugti Beds, early Miocene, Pakistan, although what this resemblance means regarding the extent of a possible relationship between the two taxa has not been explored.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D27EFDA7D4E450886F7A9D8DD5F715C6" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" type="mainText">
The taxonomic history of 
<taxonomicName id="0697135FEA2055E043E3AD76EC90A80E" authority="Pickford, 1991" authorityName="Pickford" authorityYear="1991" class="Mammalia" family="Anthracotheriidae" genus="Afromeryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Afromeryx</taxonomicName>
is complex. Pickford (1991) named 
<taxonomicName id="FB986880B78C00538228BE59BB39FC32" authority="Pickford, 1991" authorityName="Pickford" authorityYear="1991" class="Mammalia" family="Anthracotheriidae" genus="Afromeryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="africanus">Afromeryx africanus</taxonomicName>
on the basis of a right dentary with roots of p3, p4-m3 (CGM 30762), and attributed one additional sub-adult mandibular specimen (M 15021) to this species. The type specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="77F61950592BBDB71031643162775C5D" authority="Pickford, 1991" authorityName="Pickford" authorityYear="1991" class="Mammalia" family="Anthracotheriidae" genus="Afromeryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="africanus">A. africanus</taxonomicName>
had previously been recognized as representing Brachyodus 
<taxonomicName id="044D95F0BDD4586D5E3D30F7F802EDC3" authority="Pickford, 1991" authorityName="Pickford" authorityYear="1991" class="Mammalia" family="Anthracotheriidae" genus="Afromeryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="africanus">africanus</taxonomicName>
(Andrews, 1899), but Pickford (1991) stated that, 
<normalizedToken id="AA7411BF664AA757385183DEB45075D4" originalValue="‘‘">''</normalizedToken>
The material does not closely resemble Brachyodus, the molars and premolars being bunodont, the jaw being short with an unspecialized symphyseal 
<normalizedToken id="AD35E04E08904DD72B20E49606CD86DB" originalValue="region’’">region''</normalizedToken>
(1991, p. 1503). In terms of size and degree of bunodonty, we find that CGM 30762 cannot be distinguished from members of Brachyodus depereti and so we have assigned the specimen to that taxon. In addition, it is unknown how the assessment was made that CGM 30762 represented a taxon with a short jaw and an unspecialized symphyseal region. The dentary is broken in front of p3 and so is missing the anterior portion of the jaw. This is critical because many of the features that distinguish anthracothere species are located in the anterior dentition. For example, species of 
<taxonomicName id="66BD60EFC6DDD16E4F55BC55E9B4CB27" authority="Pickford, 1991" authorityName="Pickford" authorityYear="1991" class="Mammalia" family="Anthracotheriidae" genus="Afromeryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Afromeryx</taxonomicName>
have an unspecialized symphyseal region (i1-3 small, spatulate teeth, no i3-c diastema, p2 single-rooted), whereas species of Brachyodus show a number of extreme specializations (suppression of i1-2, i3 tusk-like, peglike canine, long diastema). The fact that the holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="16C8364335774E01B4CB9340AF3CCE2A" authority="Pickford, 1991" authorityName="Pickford" authorityYear="1991" class="Mammalia" family="Anthracotheriidae" genus="Afromeryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="africanus">A. africanus</taxonomicName>
designated by Pickford (1991) is a dentary with only roots of p3 and crowns p4-m3 means that most of the key diagnostic criteria of 
<taxonomicName id="535F6D5C1914F10B3A97DCE4ABA7CA59" authority="Pickford, 1991" authorityName="Pickford" authorityYear="1991" class="Mammalia" family="Anthracotheriidae" genus="Afromeryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Afromeryx</taxonomicName>
are not visible on this specimen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A19C1D6CB22577533124204B73AD2006" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" type="mainText">
Therefore, we feel that CGM 30762 cannot serve as the holotype of a species of 
<taxonomicName id="186E1904C3983D30706E759C377655D9" authority="Pickford, 1991" authorityName="Pickford" authorityYear="1991" class="Mammalia" family="Anthracotheriidae" genus="Afromeryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Afromeryx</taxonomicName>
. To rectify this situation we have reassigned CGM 30762 to Brachyodus depereti where it fits comfortably based on size and known morphology and we have assigned M15021 as the holotype and currently only know specimen of a 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="F1B1D5E862A3BC9AF7DBBBA978971633" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
of 
<taxonomicName id="88556C2164CEDFC14B7827CF784074A7" authority="Pickford, 1991" authorityName="Pickford" authorityYear="1991" class="Mammalia" family="Anthracotheriidae" genus="Afromeryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Afromeryx</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="0AD58B79488034B5B9736441791C714F" authority="Pickford, 1991" authorityName="Pickford" authorityYear="1991" class="Mammalia" family="Anthracotheriidae" genus="Afromeryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="7" pageNumber="974" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="grex">A. grex</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
